{"TopicId":55792,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Can you change map focus?","CreatedByName":"SSSPutnik","CreatedById":91745,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T06:26:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SSSPutnik","CreatedById":91745,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T06:26:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOften I find myself wanting to look at a destination in detail, is there a way to zoom on places not the current flight focus?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-12-11T06:55:46Z\u0022 title=\u002212/11/2013 06:55  AM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 11, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by SSSPutnik\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UmbralRaptor","CreatedById":2767,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T06:31:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Key_Bindings\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Etab / shift\u002Btab will cycle through bodies and your maneuver nodes. Backspace to reset.\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E(I\u0027ve included a link to the keys page on the wiki to preemptively answer additional questions)\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T06:33:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou can double click on any planet to bring it into focus, though sometimes you will accidentally switch to a ship or flag on the surface of that planet.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProbably easier is to use TAB to go through everything. You can also use shift-tab but watch out. Shift is throttle up!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEDIT: Ninja\u0027d by someone who even included a link!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSSPutnik","CreatedById":91745,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T06:55:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThanks people. Was hoping there was a way without having to focus on an object but that\u0027s fine. Cheers.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Murph","CreatedById":90837,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T07:18:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EShift-Tab will also switch to the Steam overlay after giving you some unplanned throttle, just to ensure that it does maximum damage to your mission before you realise what\u0027s happened.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSSPutnik","CreatedById":91745,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T07:34:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ELOL... Sounds about right.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kanukki","CreatedById":92482,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-11T08:23:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYep, Shift-tab has borked me on more than one occasion with the combo throttle/Steam overlay. Am I smart enough to learn and re-map the keys? Nope.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Andersenman","CreatedById":61273,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-12T11:05:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAt least you remembered. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kasuha","CreatedById":81781,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-12T11:30:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kanukki\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Kanukki\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EYep, Shift-tab has borked me on more than one occasion with the combo throttle/Steam overlay. Am I smart enough to learn and re-map the keys? Nope.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShift-Tab is safe if you use it at any (non-physics) time warp level of if you first hide the navball.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CanOmer","CreatedById":156173,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-05T12:24:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u0022823288\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002255792\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221386743499\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222767\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UmbralRaptor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11.12.2013 at 9:31 AM, UmbralRaptor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Key_Bindings\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Etab / shift\u002Btab will cycle through bodies and your maneuver nodes. Backspace to reset.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I\u0027ve included a link to the keys page on the wiki to preemptively answer additional questions)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I press shift \u002B Tab to focus previous body my craft will burn fuel.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-05T12:35:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223260175\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002255792\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221515155085\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CanOmer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, CanOmer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I press shift \u002B Tab to focus previous body my craft will burn fuel.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis thread is from 2013, also...someone answered your question way back in 2013 just above you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u0022825457\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002255792\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221386847819\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002281781\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kasuha\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/12/2013 at 6:30 AM, Kasuha said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShift-Tab is safe if you use it at any (non-physics) time warp level of if you first hide the navball.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}